HEADWORD: Shortcoming
<hw>Short"com`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
falling, or coming short</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The failure of a
crop, or the like.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Neglect of, or failure in,
performance of duty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Short-dated</ent>⟦br⟧
